               <head>Futūḥ al-Ḥaramayn by Muḥyī Lārī</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100084 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85089070">
                  <summary>A poetical guide to the Hajj pilgrimmage, written by Muḥyī al-Dīn Lārī
                     (d.1526-7), a Sufi poet who was an apprentice of <persName role="ant"
                        key="VIAF_159962989">Jalāl al-Dīn Davānī</persName>, but also a painter. The
                     work was dedicated to <persName role="dte" key="person_f8597">Muzaffar Shah II, Sultan of
                        Gujarat</persName> (r.1511-26). </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1252-item1">
                     <author key="VIAF_306119017">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Muḥyī Lārī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">محیی لاری</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_8715">Futūḥ al-Ḥaramayn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">فتوح الحرمین</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">ای همه [کس] را بدرت التجا / کعبۀ دل را ز تو نور و
                        صفا</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">صلّ علی روضة خیر الانام / خاتمۀ نسخه برین شد
                        تمام</explicit>
                     <note>
                        <p>The work has been incorrectly described as <title>Taẕkirat
                              al-Awliyāʾ</title>on the wrapper, and falsely attributed to Jāmī on
                           f.1r. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
